all the remnant BHs are retained in YSCs,\nGCs, and NSCs, respectively. The fraction of massive BHs also depends on the\nhost cluster properties, with pair-instability ($60\\leq\\,$M$_{\\rm\nBH}$/M$_{\\odot}\\leq$100) and intermediate-mass (M$_{\\rm\nBH}\\geq$100$\\,$M$_{\\odot}$) BHs accounting for approximately $\\sim44\\%$ and\n$1.6\\%$ of the mergers in YSCs, $\\sim33\\%$ and $0.7\\%$ in GCs, and $\\sim28\\%$\nand $0.4\\%$ in NSCs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Mar 2023 19:00:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-15"}
